// For an instruction like:
//   %t = fadd <2 x float> %a, %b
// a ScalarizerVisitor creates two scalar fadds:
//   %t.0 = fadd float %a.0, %b.0
//   %t.1 = fadd float %a.1, %b.1
// It refers to the scattered form of %t as { %t.0, %t.1 }.
//
// The pass is organized as a single-pass visitor that visits the instructions
// in post-order.  This allows it to visit operands before visiting the
// instructions that use them.  When visiting an instruction, it will
// (if possible) create a scattered form of its result.
//
// When the pass is complete, it replaces the original instructions with
// the scattered form.  The scattered form is then gathered together into
// a vector if the original vector result is still needed.
